
=========================
= 		INSTALL			=
=========================

---------
- LINUX -
---------

	1 - Use the LABSIM Colosse tool to generate necessary stuff. Normally you should have a network shared directory (NAS) filled with your corresponding generated XML stuff :
		- /shared-directory/my-simulation-project/InstructionSetUnit.xml
		- /shared-directory/my-simulation-project/SequentialLogicUnit.xml
		- /shared-directory/my-simulation-project/HardwireControlUnit.xml

	2 - create a local project directory, said /my/path/to/my-local-simulation-project
		
	3 - run rhea configuration script by opening a shell & type : 
		+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
		+	[user@localhost]$ rhea --project-dir=/my/path/to/my-local-simulation-project 					  +
				--ISU-file=/shared-directory/my-simulation-project/InstructionSetUnit.xml 				  	  +
				--HCU-file=/shared-directory/my-simulation-project/SequentialLogicUnit.xml 				  	  +
				--SLU-file=/shared-directory/my-simulation-project/HardwireControlUnit.xml 				  	  +
		+	[ ... ]                                                                                           +
		+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
	
	4 - then :
		+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
		+	[user@localhost]$ cd /path/to/KRONOSDSDS-source-code/											  +
		+	[user@localhost]$ mkdir build							  										  +
		+	[user@localhost]$ cd build							  											  +
		+	[user@localhost]$ cmake -DKRONOSDDS_PROJECT_DIR=/my/path/to/my-local-simulation-project ..    	  +
		+	[ ... ]                                                                                           +
		+	[user@localhost]$ make install                                                                    +
		+	[ ... ]                                                                                           +
		+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

	5 - finally, enjoy your your simulation ! 
	
-----------
- WINDOWS -
